<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                    <head>No. 324.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Brigham</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                    States Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Paso del
                                Forte</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-26"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 26, 1886</date>. (Received July
                            26.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Governor of Chihuahua pushing trial of Cutting, who ignores proceedings.
                        Result may be reached to-day. If acquitted, what do?</p>
                    <closer><signed>BRIGHAM,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Consul.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>